The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, March 29: Speaker Hashim Abdul Halim today said the controversy over his criticism of governor Gopal Krishna Gandhis statement on Nandigram was a closed chapter.

 Halim said he sent a letter with a bouquet to Gandhi last Friday, reciprocating a similar gesture by the governor.

 Calcutta: Hindustan Motors has urged striking staff of its Uttarpara unit to return to work. The company has ruled out a lockout or closure.




